\cf2 \
\
\
It was one of the most awkward conversations I've ever had. I was sitting there in a park with my dad eating my blizzard. I was told we going to get ice cream, but there was something more nefarious going on here. It was a bait and switch moment. I was getting my favorite snack while my dad was going to explain the concept of sex to me.\
\
Maybe you've had a similar experience. The one where your parents do their best, but fumble through words that should have been said a few years ago. He asked me what I knew and I lied, embarrassed about what my friends and I talked about school. In my mind there wasn't much I didn't know. It was pretty straight forward about what it was and the last thing I wanted to do was talk about it with my dad. We fumbled through "the talk" and then drove home...to never talk about sex in a meaningful way again.\
\
I learned about the same things in church. For the most part the sermons or lessons we learned were sex is something we want to avoid at all cost until marriage and if you mess it up you mess everything up. \
\
\
\
\
